headlines.description: — Khris Middleton scored a season-high 34 points against the team that drafted him, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Detroit Pistons 126-117 without Giannis Antetokounmpo on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton leads short-handed Bucks past decimated Pistons

headlines.description: - Luka Doncic started Monday hopeful he would play at Indiana.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks end 4-game skid vs. Pacers to stay in playoff hunt

events.name: Houston Rockets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored a career-high 40 points and Julius Randle had 26 as the New York Knicks snapped a three-game losing streak with a 137-115 victory over the Houston Rockets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley scores 40 in place of Brunson; Knicks beat Rockets

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 24 points and Phoenix reserves sparked the decisive run for the Suns in a 117-103 win over the fading Utah Jazz on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, bench lead Suns past skidding Jazz as Ayton returns

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic posted his 29th triple-double of the season Monday night and the Denver Nuggets beat the shorthanded Philadelphia 76ers 116-111 in a game <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid sits out, Jokic leads Nuggets past 76ers 116-111

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 29 points and the New Orleans Pelicans routed the depleted Portland Trail Blazers 124-90 on Monday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 29 as Pelicans rout Trail Blazers 124-90

headlines.description: — Jaden McDaniels scored 20 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves spoiled Sacramento's hopes for a clinching party by beating the Kings 119-115 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves win 119-115 to deny clinching party for Kings

headlines.description: - Nicolas Batum got all of his season-high 24 points on eight 3-pointers, and Eric Gordon added 22 points in the Los Angeles Clippers' comfortable 124-112 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nicolas Batum hits 8 3-pointers, Clippers beat Bulls 124-112
